16/04/2003
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- Naser Oric, 36, the commander of the Bosnian Muslim forces at Srebrenica, appeared before the UN tribunal Tuesday (15 April) to plead not guilty to six counts of violations of the law and customs of war, including murder, cruel treatment, destruction and plunder.
Arrested and transferred to The Hague by SFOR last week, Oric is charged with committing war crimes against Bosnian Serbs in Srebrenica in 1992 and 1993.
(AP, AFP, Reuters, NTV Hayat, RTRS, FoNet - 15/04/03)
